{
  "stem": "27748.2",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And we were in a boarding situation in some kind of a house-- I remember four of us in one room-- and attended school during the daytime.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There I do remember one boy, Manfred Schoenfeld.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I don't know what ever became of him.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He was in the bed next to me.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He was very nice, a roly-poly jolly fat fellow.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And everybody liked him and I liked him.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So there, we developed some-- some fraternal warmth, friendly interaction.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I think there were only boys in this school situation.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So we were there for about a month and going to some sort of a school.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Then most of us were sent to a school where I was going to stay for the next four years, Bunce Court School in Kent, [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] which was near the village of Otterden, O-T-T-E-R-D-E-N, in Kent, near Faversham, which is slightly bigger community in Kent.",
      "word_count": 48
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So that was a very unusual school.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And it-- it-- well, it was unusual for the following reason.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "In the 1920s, a Jewish woman in Germany became interested in studying education in America.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And she went to America to study education at Columbia University.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "There was a John Dewey progressive education thing.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "She studied education and became very much involved with the Quakers.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So she went back to Germany and established what was then a very progressive co-educational boarding school near Herrlingen in Germany.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And it was the new Herrlingen School that she established on very progressive basis of-- and then when Hitler came to power in 1934, 1933, shortly thereafter she moved the whole school to England, where it-- What was her name?",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Her name was Anna Essinger, E-S-S-I-N-G-E-R.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So she established a school in England.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
